node.text: @zulmochtar thanks for the prayers also praying for your country too

897 new cases of Covid-19 have been confirmed, said the Ministry of Health in a preliminary update on Friday (April 24).⁣
⁣
This brings the total number of cases here to 12,075 and is the first time in five days that the number of new daily infections dropped below 1,000.⁣
⁣
The vast majority of the new cases are work permit holders residing in foreign worker dormitories. ⁣
⁣
13 of the new cases are Singaporeans and Permanent Residents.⁣
@zulmochtar thanks for the prayers also praying for your country too
Imagine if they use St. John island which was historically used in the past as a quarantine.
@lazy._k and the community infections are getting lower is just gonna get better when people stay at home
@limmingjin I guess it is paying off.However we all can do our part by donating to charities that help the migrant workers.We can do this Singapore
At least it is lesser than the the thousands...
